description: Florida has one of the highest uninsured rates in the U.S. at 12%, representing 2.5 million people (Kaiser Family Foundation, 2016). Health centers are federally funded, community-based and patient-directed organizations that serve populations with limited access to health care, including low-income populations and the uninsured. Read more about health centers here. Use this map to explore how accessible these centers are for target populations.
subtitle: Federally funded clinics that serve vulnerable populations
dataSources: Provider Data: - U.S. HHS Health Resources & Services Administration, Feb 2018.
